Interface MathContainer

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, SBase, SBaseWithDerivedUnit, java.io.Serializable, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode, TreeNodeWithChangeSupport
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Assignment
    All Known Implementing Classes:

    public interface MathContainer
extends SBaseWithDerivedUnit
    Base interface for all the SBML components which contain MathML nodes.

    • Method Detail

      • getFormula

        @Deprecated
java.lang.String getFormula()
        Deprecated. As this is part of SBML Level 1, it is strongly recommended not to work with the String representation of a formula, but to deal with a more flexible ASTNode.
        Converts this MathContainer's internal ASTNode to a C-like String according to the SBML Level 1 specifications and returns it.
        Returns:
        the math ASTNode of this object as a String. It returns the empty String if the math ASTNode is not set.
        See Also:
        getMath()

      • getMath

        ASTNode getMath()
        If isSetMath() returns true, this method returns the ASTNode belonging to this MathContainer.
        Returns:
        the math ASTNode of this object. It return null if the math ASTNode is not set.

      • getMathMLString

        java.lang.String getMathMLString()
        If isSetMath() returns true, this method returns the corresponding MathML String, otherwise an empty String will be returned.
        Returns:
        the MathML representation of this MathContainer's math element.

      • isSetMath

        boolean isSetMath()
        Checks if an ASTNode has been set for this MathContainer.
        Returns:
        true if the math ASTNode of this object is not null.

      • setFormula

        @Deprecated
void setFormula(java.lang.String formula)
                     throws ParseException
        Deprecated. As this is part of SBML Level 1, it is strongly recommended not to work with the String representation of a formula, but to deal with a more flexible ASTNode. Please use ASTNode.parseFormula(String) to create an ASTNode object from your formula String.
        Sets the mathematical expression of this MathContainer instance to the given formula. This method parses the given String and stores the result in an ASTNode object.
        Parameters:
        formula - a C-like String according to the definition in the SBML Level 1 specifications.
        Throws:
        ParseException - If the given formula is invalid or cannot be parsed properly.
        PropertyNotAvailableException - When trying to set this attribute and the Level is set to a value other than 1, this will throw an error.
